<HEADLINE>
FT  26 APR 93 / Observer: Way out
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
In the wake of Observer's week of Swiss jokes and day of Swedish jokes, now
for a morning of Danish jokes - provided the reader who claims to have
overheard the following in Copenhagen is to be believed.
'There are three ways of doing things. The right way, the wrong way, and the
British way.'
