<HEADLINE>
FT  26 APR 93 / People: Nigel Lester quits County
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Nigel Lester, who heads County NatWest Investment Management, is leaving for
personal reasons, but has been asked by the board of NatWest Markets to stay
on for another three months while a successor is found.
The fund management operation has been hit by a string of departures, with
two other senior figures quitting just recently. David Gamble, deputy chief
executive, has left to run the British Airways Pension Fund, and Bruce
Pullman, who was in charge of quantitative product development, is moving to
Hill Samuel Life and Investment Management.
County denies that these departures are connected or reflect changing
fortunes of the operation. Total funds under management last year rose from
Pounds 12.6bn to Pounds 14bn.
Lester, 40, had been at County for three years.
</TEXT>
