<HEADLINE>
FT  26 APR 93 / Woodland battle
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CAMPAIGNERS fighting to save the 8,000-year-old Oxleas Wood in south-east
London from a road development are to take the battle to Brussels tomorrow
in a move to secure European Community backing against the government.
The move follows a High Court defeat for the residents, backed by
environmentalists, opposed to a Department of Transport plan to build a
motorway through the wood.
