<TEXT>
THE CHAIRMAN of the Commons trade and industry committee has accused the
government of subverting the authority of parliament in its handling of the
coal crisis.
Labour MP Mr Richard Caborn made the charge because of the way MPs were
denied the opportunity to vote on his committee's report on the crisis. The
government's coal white paper, published last month, largely passed over the
select committee's detailed recommendations.
Mr Caborn's charge is contained in a letter to Mr Terence Higgins, chairman
