<HEADLINE>
FT  26 APR 93 / Gays rights march
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Aids memorial quilt stretches along the Mall in Washington where,
according to police, 300,000 people marched yesterday for equal rights for
homosexuals in the US. President Bill Clinton sent a message to the
gathering: 'I stand with you in the struggle for equality for all
Americans.' But he was in Boston yesterday to speak to newspaper editors.
The president's decision not to attend angered some homosexual rights
activists, who claim he has backed away from some of his electoral campaign
promises to them, but others said it was better that Mr Clinton had stayed
away in that right-wingers would have less to use against him.
</TEXT>
