consumption expenditure, investment (the sum of gross fixed capital
formation and the change in stocks), general government final
consumption, and net exports (exports of goods and services minus
imports of goods and services). The US includes investment by
government in the government series, rather than under investment.
Quarterly GDP/GNP totals are annualised. The growth rates are the
percentage change over the corresponding period in the previous year,
and are positive unless otherwise stated. The figures in the fifth
column of each set of growth rates refer only to exports, rather than
to net exports. Data supplied by Datastream and WEFA from national
government sources.
