blue glass. Two Barclay's bank cash machines sat askew in their housings.
The window had caved in on a security shop called Bishopsgate Crime
Prevention Centre. A sign on the door said: 'How secure is your home?'
Ms Janine Barber, an executive director of IndoSuez Aval in St Helen's
Place, just off Bishopsgate and near to the centre of the blast, said: 'We
got hit by the last bomb, we've just had a burglary and now we have had this
so we've learned to cope by now.'
