were both concrete and substantial. The balance sheet had been
'significantly reshaped and strengthened'.
A share suspension last year had affected the second half with turnover for
the year falling by 12 per cent from Pounds 18.1m to Pounds 15.92m, of which
Pounds 1.62 related discontinued activities. Losses per share were 31.9p
(9.4p) and again there is no dividend.
