<HEADLINE>
FT  23 APR 93 / International Company News: Distributor takes lead in bid
for drugs wholesaler
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL ABRAHAMS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
COOPERATION Pharm-aceutique Francaise, a small French independent drugs
distributor, has emerged as the leading company in a consortium to make a
counter-bid for Office Commercial Pharmaceutique, France's largest drugs
wholesaler.
OCP is subject to a FFr2.12bn (Dollars 391m) friendly takeover from Gehe,
the German distribut-or.
CPF, with a turnover last year of FFr2.3bn, has concluded an agreement with
the Bourely family, which owns 15 per cent of OCP.
Under the agreement, the family can sell its shares in OCP and will not
participate in the consortium.
If the CPF bid is successful, the family will not sell its shares for two
years and can nominate a member of a three-man board.
One director will be appointed by CPF and the third will be chosen jointly
by the Bourely family and CPF. At the end of two years CPF will buy the
Bourely shares.
</TEXT>
